goitsemang.tlhabye@inl.co.za THE taxi industry protest march by the National Taxi Alliance has been officially suspended. The announcement was made by Acting Director-General Mathabatha Mokonyama alongside National Taxi Alliance representatives during a media briefing at the Department of Transport's offices in Pretoria this morning. Mokonyama said the march scheduled for Thursday was effectively suspended following meetings between Minister Joe Maswanganyi and the leadership of the NTA. Challenges raised by the industry regarding the public transport subsidy, taxi recapitalisation programme and compensation for operators surrendering operating licenses amongst other issues. NTA General-Secretary, Alpheus Mlalazi, added that if nothing came of engagements with the Department by November 8 then the protest action would resume.